item.title: Teleport
item.dc:creator: @I_Yaa_I I Yaa I
item.description:
@I_Yaa_I wrote:

xxpkpurexx:

finally 1 thing i yaa i does good he helped silab garaza haha … i bet u when u compile it, most of the cases wont work…

xxpkpurexx,
Your post does not contain any useful information.

Search ‘Trollheim’ and you should find something like this:

{
			if (s == "Varrock")
			{
				teleX = 3210;
				teleY = 3424;
				teletimer = 5;
				setAnimation(714);
				addSkillXP(85, 6);
				newheightLevel = 0;
			}

			if (s == "Falador")
			{
				teleX = 2964;
				teleY = 3378;
				teletimer = 5;
				setAnimation(714);
				addSkillXP(119, 6);
				newheightLevel = 0;
				
			}

			if (s == "Lumby")
			{
				teleX = 3222;
				teleY = 3218;
				teletimer = 5;
				setAnimation(714);
				addSkillXP(96, 6);
				newheightLevel = 0;
			}

			if (s == "Camelot")
			{
				teleX = 2757;
				teleY = 3477;
				teletimer = 5;
				setAnimation(714);
				addSkillXP(142, 6);
				newheightLevel = 0;
			}

			if (s == "Ardougne")
			{
				teleX = 2662;
				teleY = 3305;
				teletimer = 5;
				setAnimation(714);
				addSkillXP(159, 6);
				newheightLevel = 0;
				
			}

			if (s == "Watchtower")
			{
				teleX = 2549;
				teleY = 3113;
				teletimer = 5;
				setAnimation(714);
				addSkillXP(184, 6);
				newheightLevel = 0;
				
			}

			if (s == "Trollheim")
			{
				teleX = 2480;
				teleY = 5174;
				teletimer = 5;
				setAnimation(714);
				addSkillXP(201, 6);
				newheightLevel = 0;
			}

			if (s == "Ape")
			{
				teleX = 2761;
				teleY = 2784;
				teletimer = 5;
				setAnimation(714);
				addSkillXP(258, 6);
				newheightLevel = 0;
			}

Now, if varrock is your ‘home teleport’ then, edit the varrock:

if (s == "Varrock")
			{
				teleX = 3210;
				teleY = 3424;
				teletimer = 5;
				setAnimation(714);
				addSkillXP(85, 6);
				newheightLevel = 0;
			}

You want to make it so, you teleport to the coordinates that you want, so here:

if (s == "Varrock")
			{
				teleX = %%%%;
				teleY = %%%%;
				teletimer = 5;
				setAnimation(714);
				addSkillXP(85, 6);
				newheightLevel = 0;
			}

You must change the % to what you want the x and y axis of the coordinates you want it to be.

This is for CZAR. If you want it for something else, be more specific next time.
